{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-0210"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Silviculture and other forestry activities"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "0210"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :forestry/silviculture
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:sustainable-forestry :forest-health :rural-employment]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :forest-coordination-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:forest-ecology :identity :forms :audit-ledger :scheduling]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "ForestryAdvisor ⊣ Forest Coordination Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A BACK-OFFICE COORDINATION actor
 for community silviculture operations (stand assessment -> field-
 operation scheduling (planting/thinning/harvest) -> forest-health
 monitoring -> supply procurement) -- not direct logging-equipment or
 field-operation control authority; `:itonami.blueprint/robotics` is
 honestly `false` (see README `What this actor does NOT do`). Four ops
 (`:log-stand-record` / `:schedule-field-operation` / `:flag-forest-
 health-concern` / `:order-supplies`), all `:effect :propose` only.
 Nine concrete governor checks (`forestry.governor`) elaborate this
 blueprint's HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct logging-
 equipment control), permanent harvest-finalize block, independent
 stand-verification check before any field-operation scheduling,
 independent stand-maturity recompute (`forestry.registry/maturity-
 threshold-years`, 20 years) for harvest eligibility, double-schedule
 guard, closed health-status validation, and independent supply-order
 total recompute against its own line items. Forest-health-concern
 flagging ALWAYS escalates to a human forester regardless of
 confidence, and any supply order whose independently-recomputed total
 exceeds `forestry.registry/supply-order-cost-threshold` (5000.0)
 escalates too; `:log-stand-record` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean
 (`forestry.phase`). No external `kotoba-lang/forestry`-style capability
 library exists to wrap (see docs/adr/0001-architecture.md Decision 1)
 -- domain logic is self-contained pure functions in `forestry.registry`,
 re-verified independently by `forestry.governor`, backed by a single
 `MemStore` (`forestry.store`). Verified: `clojure -M:test` green
 (64 tests, 160 assertions, 0 failures, 0 errors as of 2026-07-22)."}
